The increment operator (++) and decrement operator (--) are for incrementing and decrementing a variable by 1.

Operator	Name	        Description	Example
++var	    Preincrement	Increment var by 1, and use the new var value in the statement	int j = ++i;
			                // j is 2, i is 2
Var++	    Postincrement	Increment var by 1, but use the original var value in the statement	int j = i++;
			                // j is 1, i is 2
--var	    Predecrement	Decrement var by 1, and use the new var value in the statement	int j = --i;
			                // j = 0, i is 0
Var--	    Postdecrement	Decrement var by 1, and use the original var value in the statement	int j = i--
			                // j = 1, i = 0

